snippet.textDisplay: Here’s the tea. I live and work in LA and was on the set of the REACT video and all the girls really do get along and root for each other, yes even Nicole. Some history for all you youngins: Carmit has been with PCD since the burlesque troupe began in 1995. Ashley, Jessica and Kimberly joined the troupe later. When the concept of a girl group came about, Melody and Nicole were added, obviously adding stronger vocals for the group. I had a physical copy of the PCD album when I was 12 and remember reading the credits in the inside cover which credited Nicole/Melody/Carmit with vocals and Jessica/Kimberly/Ashley with background vocals. I think even Kaya Jones (who used to be in the troupe back in the day) was credited with background vocals. She’s credited on Wiki but that’s another story lol. So it was never a surprise to me that Nicole's voice was prominently featured. AND HELLO… I have ears lol. I can hear that Nicole's voice was prominently featured. So idk why people were surprised when Nicole "revealed" on “VH1 Driven” that she was the only one singing 99% of vocals. It is what it is. And I loved it and didn’t care lol. Also, Melody was the only one without dance experience and was younger than everyone. Imagine being in a group of PROFESSIONAL dancers and having no dance experience. They probably had to work around Melody’s skill level and I can only imagine how Melody must have felt sometimes. Regardless, Melody totally had me fooled and I always assumed she had dance experience! I actually saw Melody the day the video dropped and she seemed fine. I respect her choice not to come back. And that’s all I have to say about all that.
